Definition: any of a series of nerve agents containing organophosphate compounds first synthesized by German chemists in 1936
Example: in World War II the Germans tested them in concentration camps but not on the battlefield; Iraq is alleged to have used them against Iran and against the Kurds
Synonyms: nerve_gas, any, of, a, series, nerve, agents, containing, organophosphate, compounds, first, synthesized, by, German, chemists, in, World, War, II, the, Germans, tested, them, concentration, camps, but, not, on, battlefield, Iraq, is, alleged, to, have, used, against, Iran, and, Kurds
Category: noun.substance
